      /&gt;
    &lt;/span&gt;
  &lt;/span&gt;
  
  &lt;/a&gt;
    &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;h3&gt;Importing Root SSL Certificate to Firefox&lt;/h3&gt;
&lt;ol&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Type this in url bar of firefox and press enter. &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;gatsby-highlight&quot; data-language=&quot;text&quot;&gt;
      &lt;pre class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;&lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;about:preferences#privacy&lt;/code&gt;&lt;/pre&gt;
      &lt;/div&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now scroll down to Certifiactes(under security) and click on ‚ÄúView Certifiactes‚Äù.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Now go to the tab ‚ÄúAuthorities‚Äù. This contains all the CAs that browser trusts. We will import our CA (cacert.pem) into this.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Click on import. Choose the &lt;code class=&quot;language-text&quot;&gt;cacert.pem&lt;/code&gt; file.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;
